The risk of rejecting is clear: the worst-case outcome is zero dollars, while the best-case outcome (if RED improves their offer) is still speculative and not guaranteed. In contrast, accepting the 10-dollar offer guarantees a positive payoff with zero risk. This aligns with the **Nash bargaining solution** for ultimatum games, where accepting any non-zero offer is the dominant strategy in a one-time interaction with no outside options.

Additionally, my move structure is constrained:
